WEBVTT

01:49.401 --> 01:51.642
<i>MAN: AH right, people.
This is Agent Ford.</i>

01:51.737 --> 01:54.229
<i>We're almost there.
Let's make it count.</i>

01:56.074 --> 01:58.691
<i>This is a surveillance op.
We do not want this guy.</i>

01:58.785 --> 02:02.449
<i>I repeat, do not let him l.D.
you. He's just the driver.</i>

02:02.539 --> 02:04.621
<i>Eagle One.
Gimme a heads-up.</i>

02:04.708 --> 02:06.745
Eagle One has
target in sight.

02:07.753 --> 02:09.994
Target moving east
on Third. Over.

02:10.088 --> 02:12.045
<i>Roger, Eagle One.</i>

02:14.301 --> 02:18.260
<i>C.P. is following. Packages
are right there in the back.</i>

02:46.541 --> 02:49.124
FORD: Eagle One, you copy
the black Mustang?

02:50.879 --> 02:53.166
EAGLE <i>ONE: Roger, C-P- There's</i>
a <i>second one closing in also.</i>

02:59.638 --> 03:00.969
Shit!

03:05.644 --> 03:07.681
FORD: He's made us.
Maintain pursuit.

03:07.771 --> 03:09.887
Repeat, maintain pursuit.

03:12.984 --> 03:14.850
Get the plates
on those Mustangs!

03:20.325 --> 03:22.862
Do not lose that driver. He's
our only link to the buyers.

03:33.088 --> 03:34.169
(HORN BLARING)

04:20.761 --> 04:21.796
(GRUNTS)

04:28.727 --> 04:30.968
FBI! Freeze! Freeze!

04:31.062 --> 04:32.973
Don't shoot! ATF!

04:33.064 --> 04:34.805
Agent McClaren, ATF.

04:34.900 --> 04:36.982
What the hell's ATF doin'
on an FBI operation?

04:37.068 --> 04:38.308
And you are?

04:38.403 --> 04:39.814
Allen Ford.

04:40.280 --> 04:43.363
You know, I'm sensing a lot
of hostility here, Allen.

04:43.450 --> 04:44.861
There's no reason
to get defensive.

04:44.951 --> 04:48.945
You've got yourself a dead driver
and a cute little shipment of guns!

04:49.039 --> 04:50.404
But you don't
have the seller,

04:50.499 --> 04:51.785
and you don't
have the buyer!

04:52.083 --> 04:54.666
All you've done is shown
the man we're onto him.

04:54.753 --> 04:57.245
ATF! What does that
stand for, anyway?

04:57.339 --> 04:59.501
Alcohol, Tobacco
and Fuckups?

04:59.591 --> 05:01.753
(SIRENS BLARING)

05:01.843 --> 05:04.210
Definitely a lot
of hostility.

05:04.471 --> 05:06.758
(FOGHORN WAILING)

05:09.518 --> 05:11.759
(SHIP HORN BLARING)

05:20.153 --> 05:22.110
MAN:
Change your nozzle!

05:31.122 --> 05:34.456
Hey, Tommy, you're takin' a little
longer than you should with that!

05:34.543 --> 05:36.204
Let's go! Let's go!

05:39.881 --> 05:41.963
Come on. Come on!

05:42.342 --> 05:43.924
Come on! Let's go!

05:44.010 --> 05:46.047
MAN: Find out what
that problem was?

05:46.137 --> 05:48.003
MAN 1:
Supposed to be 3/16ths!

05:48.098 --> 05:51.307
VINCE: Jeff, do I have to remind
you what happened last week?

05:51.518 --> 05:53.384
(RATCHET CLICKING)

05:53.478 --> 05:55.719
Come on, Billy.
Get a mop and clean that up.

05:58.316 --> 06:00.353
Crews!
Yeah.

06:00.443 --> 06:02.059
I need this one today.

06:02.487 --> 06:04.728
MAN: Manuel,
main-end rod bearing!

06:05.740 --> 06:07.196
Mr. Cutler said tomorrow.

06:07.284 --> 06:08.900
I don't give a shit
what Mr. Cutler said.

06:08.994 --> 06:11.827
I got a bunch of loads going out.
I need this one today.

06:14.374 --> 06:16.285
(MUTTERS)
Is that a problem?

06:17.168 --> 06:18.909
Uh, no, sir...

06:19.004 --> 06:22.463
It's just I told my wife I'd pick
my daughter up from school and...

06:22.549 --> 06:23.914
Well, that's real
fatherly of you,

06:24.009 --> 06:25.420
but if you want
to keep this job,

06:25.510 --> 06:27.000
you're gonna stay here
till it's finished.

06:28.305 --> 06:29.921
MAN: Hey, Greg, can you
give me a hand over here?

06:30.015 --> 06:31.597
If you need it,
it'll be done.

06:37.856 --> 06:39.017
Mr. Cutler wanted
to see me?

06:39.107 --> 06:41.269
He's expecting you, Jack.

06:41.359 --> 06:42.849
(KNOCKING)
Come in!

06:44.237 --> 06:45.978
(PHONE RINGING)

06:51.244 --> 06:53.110
Yes, sir.
You wanted to see me?

06:53.580 --> 06:54.820
Sit down, Crews.

07:03.173 --> 07:04.880
You've been with me, what,
Crews, three weeks now?

07:04.966 --> 07:06.127
Yes, sir.

07:06.217 --> 07:08.299
Says here, you used
to drive a truck.

07:08.386 --> 07:11.003
I think, uh, "used to drive"
is the operative phrase.

07:11.431 --> 07:12.796
Come on, Jack.
Don't be so modest.

07:12.891 --> 07:13.972
Your parole officer
says you could drive

07:14.059 --> 07:16.266
an ice truck through hell
on the 4th of July.

07:16.895 --> 07:18.761
Bet you miss that life,
don't you?

07:19.064 --> 07:21.431
Being your own boss and nobody
tellin' you what to do.

07:22.150 --> 07:23.311
Sometimes, I guess.

07:23.860 --> 07:25.442
I bet you miss the money
all the time.

07:27.656 --> 07:30.398
How'd you like a chance
to earn some extra cash?

07:31.159 --> 07:33.571
I got a load I need
brought up from Atlanta.

07:34.079 --> 07:35.285
Off the books,
you know what I mean?

07:36.498 --> 07:38.080
Sir, if you know
I can drive,

07:38.166 --> 07:41.830
you also know that I lost my license
permanently when I went to prison.

07:41.920 --> 07:45.504
The way I see it, you only need a
license if you get pulled over.

07:45.590 --> 07:47.331
You've made that Georgia
run before, right?

07:47.425 --> 07:48.506
You know how easy it is.

07:48.593 --> 07:50.834
It's 15 hours. Nobody even has
to know you're out of town.

07:50.929 --> 07:53.136
Not even your parole officer.
Nobody.

07:54.307 --> 07:55.638
I don't think so.

07:57.769 --> 07:59.385
I'll tell you
what I'll do, Jack.

08:00.438 --> 08:02.520
I know some people.
Do this for me,

08:02.607 --> 08:04.348
I might be able to get
your license back.

08:04.651 --> 08:06.608
Job pays 10 grand.

08:07.112 --> 08:08.602
I can't do it.

08:09.114 --> 08:11.025
(LAUGHS)

08:12.409 --> 08:14.400
Why don't you sleep
on it, Jack?

08:15.453 --> 08:16.693
Seein' how much
you like your job,

08:16.788 --> 08:18.995
I'd hate to see you
make the wrong decision.

08:21.126 --> 08:23.083
Why don't you check
with me tomorrow?

08:32.761 --> 08:34.503
Federal Bureau
of Investigation.

08:34.597 --> 08:36.008
WOMAN: DNA is a match.

08:36.099 --> 08:38.090
MAN: One moment,
Hlcheck.

08:38.183 --> 08:39.640
Today! Today.

08:40.979 --> 08:43.812
Excuse me, Holly, is this the file?
Yes. That's it. Yeah.

08:44.482 --> 08:46.894
From now on you'll be
working with ATF on this.

08:46.985 --> 08:49.693
With all due respect, I know
we've had our setbacks,

08:49.779 --> 08:53.443
but the ATF directly
interfered with our operation.

08:53.533 --> 08:54.739
What happened
was their fault.

08:54.826 --> 08:56.567
I'm hearing your
defensive voice again.

08:56.661 --> 08:57.776
I am not being defensive!

08:57.871 --> 08:59.908
You say that whenever you're
getting defensive, Allen.

08:59.998 --> 09:01.955
You want me to be defensive?
All right.

09:02.042 --> 09:05.330
You might see yourself <i>as</i> all
over the 6:00 news on this thing,

09:05.420 --> 09:06.581
but the reality is,

09:06.671 --> 09:08.582
you're putting a serious
operation at risk.

09:08.673 --> 09:11.040
Now, I'm hearing some very
real masculinity issues.

09:11.509 --> 09:13.841
What the hell's
the matter with you?

09:14.637 --> 09:17.129
Look, we've got a lead
on another shipment.

09:17.223 --> 09:19.180
We don't need
this interference.

09:19.267 --> 09:21.725
Allen, this is hardly
my call, okay?

09:22.520 --> 09:26.639
Coordinate your efforts with Agent
MoClaren, and you'll both report to me.

09:26.733 --> 09:28.599
That's the way
it's gonna be!

09:28.693 --> 09:29.899
(PHONES RINGING)

09:29.986 --> 09:32.523
MAN: I agree with you.
Very little I can do.

09:33.782 --> 09:35.864
(TIMER BUZZES)
MELANIE: Tracy, dinner!

09:36.951 --> 09:38.908
Hi. What are we having?

09:38.995 --> 09:41.282
Only the absolute best,
homemade.

09:41.831 --> 09:44.072
Did you wash
yourhands?

09:44.167 --> 09:45.874
How's practice?
Good!

09:45.960 --> 09:47.450
Yeah?
Yeah.

09:48.213 --> 09:51.376
Hey, Dad, can you help me
with my foul shots tomorrow?

09:51.758 --> 09:52.998
We have a game on Friday.

09:54.052 --> 09:55.213
Yeah. You bet.

09:56.429 --> 09:57.919
I'm not missin' this one.

09:58.598 --> 09:59.963
(GIGGLES)

10:00.642 --> 10:02.303
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

10:07.565 --> 10:10.227
You truly are gorgeous.
You know that?

10:21.996 --> 10:23.578
Do you remember...
Hmm?

10:24.082 --> 10:25.993
...that night
at Grover's Point?

10:26.084 --> 10:27.666
Mmm-hmm.

10:27.752 --> 10:29.743
The thunder
and the lightning...

10:30.547 --> 10:31.708
BOTH: And the candles.

10:31.798 --> 10:33.914
(LAUGHING)

10:37.220 --> 10:38.836
(WHISPERING)
Be right back.

11:01.452 --> 11:03.068
"Foreclosure."

11:12.463 --> 11:14.921
I wanted to tell you,
but I

11:15.717 --> 11:17.674
thought you should have
some breathing room first.

11:20.471 --> 11:22.087
$9,000?

11:23.683 --> 11:26.425
After they cut my hours, I
just couldn't make ends meet.

11:27.645 --> 11:30.854
Oh, my God! Melanie, why didn't
you say something? I could've...

11:30.940 --> 11:33.682
You could've what, Jack?
You were inside.

11:37.155 --> 11:40.489
Look, we'll rent a place back in Newark
till we can get back on our feet.

11:40.575 --> 11:41.656
We'll make it work.

11:41.743 --> 11:43.199
No. No.

11:44.204 --> 11:46.787
We moved out of Newark
so Tracy could have a yard

11:46.873 --> 11:49.535
and go to a school without
metal detectors in the halls.

11:49.626 --> 11:51.617
We are not going back!

11:51.711 --> 11:54.829
I worked my ass off for this. I'm
not gonna let us lose this house.

11:55.173 --> 11:58.507
Jack, even with what we both
make, we are too far behind.

12:01.387 --> 12:03.469
I was offered
a job today,

12:04.474 --> 12:05.839
driving.

12:07.685 --> 12:09.551
One load.
Atlanta to here.

12:10.355 --> 12:11.470
Cash.

12:12.523 --> 12:15.436
Melanie, I'll make enough
money to get us out of this.

12:16.527 --> 12:19.690
The last time you said one
more load then we'd be okay,

12:21.324 --> 12:22.485
we weren't.

12:26.371 --> 12:28.362
I can't go
through that again.

12:38.716 --> 12:40.923
(THUNDERCLAP)

12:45.890 --> 12:47.722
(CHATTERING ON RADIO)

12:51.604 --> 12:53.811
(ANIMAL GROWLING)

13:00.446 --> 13:02.938
(ANIMAL SNARLING)

13:05.827 --> 13:07.534
(DOG SNARLING)

13:11.457 --> 13:12.913
(TIRES SCREECHING)

13:13.418 --> 13:14.624
(THUNDERCLAP)

13:14.711 --> 13:16.293
(PANTING)

13:41.195 --> 13:43.106
(JET ENGINES ROARING)

13:57.795 --> 14:00.287
<i>Tryin' to make a livin'</i>

14:00.381 --> 14:03.123
<i>That's the bottom line</i>

14:03.217 --> 14:05.333
<i>It ain't easy tryin' to
stretch a nickel into a dime</i>

14:05.428 --> 14:06.543
Appreciate it.
Y'all take care.

14:08.931 --> 14:13.767
<i>Sweatin' for a dollar
Workin' for the man</i>

14:14.312 --> 14:19.102
<i>Half goes to the landlord
and half to Uncle Sam</i>

14:19.192 --> 14:24.107
<i>I can't get no consolation
I don't get no faith again</i>

14:24.739 --> 14:26.696
<i>I can't get no satisfaction
and my tractor...</i>

14:26.783 --> 14:28.069
MAN: King me. King me.

14:28.493 --> 14:30.075
Earl back yet?
No.

14:31.621 --> 14:34.329
I need them damn
Sunday throwaways.

14:35.416 --> 14:37.248
You gonna play, or you
gonna do somethin' else?

14:37.335 --> 14:39.121
You the driver
from New Jersey?

14:39.212 --> 14:40.418
That's me.

14:40.838 --> 14:41.873
You got a name?

14:41.964 --> 14:43.204
Jack Crews.

14:43.966 --> 14:45.206
(HAMMERING)

14:48.054 --> 14:50.546
"And they shall beat their
swords into plowshares."

14:52.016 --> 14:53.347
Isaiah 2:4.

14:54.102 --> 14:55.684
You read your Bible?

14:56.604 --> 14:57.810
Probably not as much
as I should.

14:58.272 --> 15:00.058
You try and lead
a good life?

15:00.942 --> 15:02.023
When I can.

15:03.528 --> 15:05.485
That's the most
important thing.

15:07.281 --> 15:08.737
(ENGINE WHINING)
Excuse me, Mr. Crews.

15:12.370 --> 15:13.405
Where have you been?

15:13.496 --> 15:14.827
Puttin' her
through her paces.

15:14.914 --> 15:16.780
This ain't
a damn NASCAR rally.

15:16.874 --> 15:18.865
Did you get
my Sunday throwaways?

15:18.960 --> 15:20.166
You know,
it slipped my mind.

15:20.253 --> 15:21.664
It slipped your mind?

15:22.046 --> 15:25.380
Did you know there's coupons for 50
cents off luncheon meats at Winn-Dixie?

15:26.092 --> 15:28.208
I ask you to do
one simple thing.

15:31.431 --> 15:33.263
Mr. Cutler
sent us a driver.

15:34.851 --> 15:36.341
Earl. Jack Crews.

15:38.104 --> 15:39.594
You'll have to forgive
Earl's manners.

15:40.106 --> 15:42.473
He was hopin' he'd get to drive.
(CHUCKLES)

15:45.069 --> 15:47.731
Uh, I'm not takin' that.
What?

15:48.030 --> 15:49.441
It's brand-spankin' new.

15:51.033 --> 15:52.819
I don't need
that kind of attention.

15:53.828 --> 15:57.537
Junior, come down here and
show Jack Crews a tractor

15:57.623 --> 15:59.534
that's more
to his likin'.

16:00.835 --> 16:01.825
Come on.

16:06.632 --> 16:10.500
RED: I think Mr. Cutler suspects something.
He sent down a new driver.

16:10.595 --> 16:13.178
<i>MAN OVER PHONE: It don't make a damn bit
of difference, Red. Our deal's with you.</i>

16:13.264 --> 16:14.925
I know that.

16:15.516 --> 16:19.009
Things are gettin' more complicated now.
I'm gonna need some more cash.

16:19.103 --> 16:21.265
<i>You listen to me. 6:00
tonight with that truck</i>

16:21.355 --> 16:23.722
<i>or cash 'II be
the last thing you need.</i>

16:25.026 --> 16:26.312
So, what's it got in it?

16:26.402 --> 16:29.611
3406 "Cat," turbo-ed,
four and a quarter,

16:29.697 --> 16:31.938
Fuller-Eaton 10-speed,
pro-shift.

16:32.033 --> 16:33.148
Got a Jake brake?

16:33.242 --> 16:34.528
Yep-

16:35.786 --> 16:37.197
How are the brakes?

16:37.288 --> 16:38.995
New. Put 'em on myself.

16:39.081 --> 16:40.116
And the rubber?

16:40.208 --> 16:42.700
Almost new.
Ain't no recaps.

16:44.545 --> 16:47.082
All right.
Fire her up.

16:49.300 --> 16:51.382
(ENGINE REVVING)

17:03.105 --> 17:04.971
Earl's gonna be
riding with ya.

17:05.066 --> 17:06.897
What do you mean, he's
gonna be riding with me?

17:06.983 --> 17:09.021
Somebody has to drive
that tractor home.

17:10.655 --> 17:11.986
Right as rain.

17:17.118 --> 17:19.234
Sonny's here.
I guess we can hit it.

17:22.040 --> 17:23.497
You're late.

17:23.751 --> 17:27.415
Yeah, yeah, I know. I may be
late, but I'm always on time.

17:27.505 --> 17:29.462
Hey, Wes. (LAUGHS)
WES: Hey, Earl.

17:30.967 --> 17:32.457
Who's that?

17:32.552 --> 17:33.917
He's drivin'.

17:34.011 --> 17:35.501
Since when?
Since an hour ago.

17:36.806 --> 17:38.046
Came down from the top.

17:38.266 --> 17:39.256
From the top of what?

17:39.350 --> 17:41.057
You make him seem like
he's goddamned Moses.

17:41.269 --> 17:42.976
Don't you take
the Lord's name in vain.

17:43.104 --> 17:44.640
Well, I'm goddamned sorry.

17:44.939 --> 17:49.433
Well, you gonna be sorry. If you don't
like it, Sonny, you can get out right now.

17:49.527 --> 17:51.859
What I don't like is you,
him or anybody else

17:51.946 --> 17:54.278
changing the plans every time I turn
around. That's what I don't like.

17:56.409 --> 17:57.899
I'm Sonny.

17:57.994 --> 17:59.610
And I'm Wes.

17:59.704 --> 18:01.286
And I'm Jack Crews.

18:02.206 --> 18:05.665
We'll be cruisin' right behind you.
Cruisin' behind the Crews.

18:05.751 --> 18:06.786
(WES LAUGHING)

18:06.877 --> 18:08.038
What do ya mean,
you'll be right behind me?

18:08.296 --> 18:09.627
RED: Protection.

18:09.714 --> 18:10.954
Protection from what?

18:11.382 --> 18:14.249
It's policy. We send
a car with every truck.

18:17.388 --> 18:19.220
Come on. Let's do it.

18:36.282 --> 18:38.398
(DOG BARKING)

18:43.122 --> 18:44.157
This your dog?

18:44.248 --> 18:46.910
Tiny ain't nobody's
dog but his own.

18:47.793 --> 18:49.409
Easy, b0)'-

18:49.795 --> 18:53.208
Toilets. Can you believe it?
Five-gallon flush.

18:55.760 --> 18:58.127
Wanna look any closer?

18:58.220 --> 18:59.961
I'm just here to drive.

19:06.812 --> 19:11.147
<i>I was born on a bus
they say goin' south</i>

19:11.233 --> 19:16.524
<i>Left at a truck stop
I never knew my mother</i>

19:16.614 --> 19:20.482
<i>And ever since
the highway's been my home</i>

19:22.119 --> 19:26.488
<i>Like a restless wind
I keep movin' on and I</i>

19:26.957 --> 19:32.794
<i>Can't seem to stay
in one place too long</i>

19:33.005 --> 19:35.622
<i>I'm a road man</i>

19:36.926 --> 19:42.217
<i>Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah</i>

19:47.812 --> 19:49.894
Over there,
you have your starter.

19:50.356 --> 19:53.974
Down there's your clutch,
brake, go pedal.

19:55.486 --> 19:57.193
Thanks for reminding me.

19:57.697 --> 19:59.187
Let's see what ya got.

20:12.086 --> 20:13.417
(ENGINE STARTS)

20:23.723 --> 20:25.179
(AIR WHOOSHES)

20:25.850 --> 20:26.840
(SIGHS)

20:33.190 --> 20:34.396
(SIGHS)

20:35.901 --> 20:38.643
(ENGINE STALLS)

20:39.864 --> 20:41.821
I thought
you could drive.

20:44.368 --> 20:45.574
First time.

20:59.467 --> 21:02.255
This driver comin' down,
does that change things?

21:02.762 --> 21:05.345
You're not plannin' on
havin' kids, are ya, Junior?

21:05.431 --> 21:08.423
I don't know. Find the
right woman, maybe.

21:08.768 --> 21:09.974
Why?

21:10.060 --> 21:13.178
'Cause you suffer from a
sorry-ass lack of balls.

21:15.649 --> 21:19.017
<i>Well, the midnight headlights
blinds you on a rainy night</i>

21:19.111 --> 21:23.355
<i>Steep grade up ahead
Slow me down, makin' no time</i>

21:23.949 --> 21:27.317
<i>But I gotta keep rollin'</i>

21:27.745 --> 21:31.079
<i>Those windshield wipers
slappin' out a tempo</i>

21:31.165 --> 21:34.908
<i>Keepin' perfect rhythm
with the song on the radio</i>

21:35.795 --> 21:39.333
<i>Yeah, I gotta keep rollin'</i>

21:40.049 --> 21:44.418
<i>Ooh, I'm drivin'
my life away</i>

21:45.221 --> 21:47.713
<i>Lookin' for a better way</i>

21:48.349 --> 21:50.340
<i>For me</i>

21:52.728 --> 21:54.890
"Virgo. Today's
the day to begin

21:54.980 --> 21:57.438
"a business relationship
with a new friend."

21:59.068 --> 22:00.399
Guess you're
my new friend.

22:06.575 --> 22:09.943
<i>Well, the truck stop cutie
comin' on to me</i>

22:10.037 --> 22:13.450
<i>Tried to talk me into a ride
Said I wouldn't be sorry</i>

22:14.291 --> 22:15.531
We in the middle of
committing a felony.

22:15.626 --> 22:16.741
That's what you
want to do, litter?

22:16.836 --> 22:18.042
We're not
committing anything.

22:18.128 --> 22:20.119
We're just
following a truck.

22:20.214 --> 22:21.750
Yeah, right.

22:21.841 --> 22:24.048
You wanna play Pididdle?
Pi... What?

22:24.134 --> 22:27.377
Pididdle... You see a car with one
headlight, you yell "Pididdle."

22:27.471 --> 22:29.212
First one to yell wins.

22:29.640 --> 22:31.222
It's daylight, Wes.

22:32.309 --> 22:33.720
Ya got a point.

22:34.979 --> 22:38.813
(LAUGHS)
I got it. Yes.

22:41.110 --> 22:43.727
This is what I do.
This is my passion.

22:43.821 --> 22:45.778
I'm a...
I'm a songwriter.

22:46.490 --> 22:48.026
That's what I do.

22:48.409 --> 22:49.649
Listen to this.

22:50.536 --> 22:55.246
<i>Do you still read my horoscope
in the paper every mornin'</i>

22:55.583 --> 22:58.041
<i>To see exactly
what I'm gonna do</i>

22:59.086 --> 23:04.707
<i>Do you still read my horoscope
in the paper every mornin'</i>

23:05.342 --> 23:09.381
<i>To see if I'll be
comin' home to you</i>

23:11.223 --> 23:12.338
What do you think?

23:13.434 --> 23:17.098
Uh, I... I don't listen
to very much country music.

23:17.855 --> 23:20.096
Well, I do.
Take my word for it.

23:20.190 --> 23:21.806
This is the beginning
of a good song.

23:22.026 --> 23:24.267
See, a good song has
to have a good hook.

23:24.361 --> 23:25.442
That's what it's all about.

23:25.779 --> 23:29.113
You reach out and you grab
'em with "horoscope."

23:29.199 --> 23:30.815
See, you give 'em
the twist...

23:31.493 --> 23:32.858
Pull over, would you?
I gotta take a leak.

23:32.953 --> 23:33.943
Again?

23:34.038 --> 23:35.824
I got a bladder
the size of a pea.

23:39.001 --> 23:41.288
Breaker 1-9 from 10-36.

23:42.713 --> 23:44.044
What do you want?

23:44.548 --> 23:46.289
<i>SONNY".
Wes has to drain his lily.</i>

23:50.721 --> 23:52.553
Think I'll hit
the head too.

23:56.226 --> 23:58.558
I'm gonna see if they
got any books on tape.

24:00.564 --> 24:03.181
All that stuff about Moses
and all that.

24:03.275 --> 24:05.357
That wasn't personal,
you understand.

24:06.111 --> 24:07.772
No problem.

24:07.863 --> 24:09.194
I just wish for once
these clowns

24:09.281 --> 24:11.238
would stick to the plan,
you know what I'm sayin'?

24:11.325 --> 24:12.907
I hear you.

24:14.244 --> 24:15.575
Hello!

24:15.663 --> 24:18.325
(CHUCKLES) Hello.
Come to Papa!

24:18.415 --> 24:19.905
In your dreams, Wes.

24:25.255 --> 24:28.498
<i>He's been gone
for 10 long days</i>

24:30.010 --> 24:33.253
<i>Burnin' up that interstate</i>

24:34.765 --> 24:37.974
<i>He's got a run
from coast to coast</i>

24:39.520 --> 24:41.306
<i>I got one more night to go</i>

24:41.397 --> 24:43.889
See, I told you we could
play Pididdle in the day.

24:44.024 --> 24:45.059
What?

24:45.150 --> 24:46.857
Pididdle, right behind us.

24:49.947 --> 24:50.937
(GUN COCKING)

24:51.115 --> 24:52.105
Oh!

24:54.368 --> 24:55.779
What the...

25:01.125 --> 25:02.661
(GRUNTS)
(GLASS SHATTERS)

25:09.717 --> 25:11.048
(HORN BLARES)

25:11.135 --> 25:12.421
(TIRES SCREECHING)

25:13.554 --> 25:14.965
(GRUNTING)

25:35.576 --> 25:36.782
(SCREAMS)

25:47.921 --> 25:49.082
Uh-oh.

25:52.051 --> 25:53.166
(BOTH GRUNT)

26:00.434 --> 26:03.347
That's D.W. and Leroy
from Red's place.

26:03.520 --> 26:05.102
What the hell
are they doin'?

26:07.566 --> 26:08.806
Now, we got ya.

26:28.754 --> 26:29.789
(GRUNTS)

26:30.089 --> 26:31.796
(ENGINE REVVING)

26:41.725 --> 26:42.760
That Red's truck?

26:43.143 --> 26:44.759
He's tryin' to
hflacktheload.

26:45.062 --> 26:46.223
Good 0l'
Southern hospitality.

26:53.403 --> 26:54.438
<i>Crews'?</i>

26:57.699 --> 26:58.860
Huh? Jeez!

27:02.037 --> 27:03.152
What are ya doin'?

27:05.415 --> 27:06.576
(GRUNTING)

27:07.417 --> 27:08.748
Oh!

27:11.880 --> 27:13.416
Son of a bitch!

27:21.348 --> 27:24.215
What the hell you waitin' on?
Move it! Move it!

27:24.309 --> 27:27.301
Let's go! Let's go! Get out
of that truck! Come on!

27:30.941 --> 27:35.185
I should've seen this comin'. For all
that talk of Jesus, Red is a greedy man.

27:45.080 --> 27:46.411
(GRUNTING)

27:49.626 --> 27:51.333
(TIRES SCREECHING)

27:57.718 --> 28:01.302
Sonny, next time he backs off, floor it.
Can you do that?

28:01.805 --> 28:02.886
Okay, I'm gonna try!

28:04.641 --> 28:05.676
Watch out!

28:07.769 --> 28:08.759
Sonny, now!

28:08.854 --> 28:10.219
Go!Go!Go!

28:13.650 --> 28:16.108
(TIRES SCREECHING)

28:27.789 --> 28:29.905
Yeah. You can drive.

28:30.584 --> 28:32.245
It's comin' back to me.

28:44.514 --> 28:47.302
Damn! Look what he did
to my car, man!

28:48.227 --> 28:49.717
Can't believe this!

28:49.811 --> 28:51.347
Will you look at this?

28:53.232 --> 28:54.939
If people are willing
to kill me to get this load,

28:55.025 --> 28:57.266
I ought to know exactly
what they want.

29:12.376 --> 29:15.038
"The gates of Babylon
shall not be shut."

29:16.380 --> 29:18.371
That son of a bitch
can drive.

29:18.882 --> 29:21.749
We're gonna have to work a
little harder to get that load.

29:21.843 --> 29:23.049
Maybe we ought
to give up.

29:23.136 --> 29:27.801
Junior, never underestimate
the power of prayer.

29:32.396 --> 29:33.727
(BARKING)

29:33.814 --> 29:36.852
Hey, Tiny. Rough ride,
wasn't it, boy?

30:01.008 --> 30:02.339
What a surprise.

30:03.802 --> 30:06.760
AK-47,
Chinese assault rifles.

30:06.847 --> 30:08.429
Twelve rounds per second.

30:09.057 --> 30:12.345
One tug on this baby,
and it'll cut you in half.

30:12.436 --> 30:13.767
Box it up.

30:25.615 --> 30:26.650
<i>(ON PHONE)
Yeah, Frank Cutler.</i>

30:26.742 --> 30:28.073
Yeah, it's Crews.

30:28.160 --> 30:30.777
Hey, good to hear from ya, Jack.
How's everything?

30:30.871 --> 30:33.238
Well, I did have a little
run-in with your friend, Red.

30:33.332 --> 30:35.448
It seems he's tryin'
to hijack your load.

30:36.251 --> 30:37.286
Is the load okay?

30:37.502 --> 30:40.119
You didn't tell me I'd be
hauling illegal artillery.

30:40.297 --> 30:42.379
Well, the truth is, Jack,
if you wanted to know

30:42.466 --> 30:44.457
what was in the back of that
truck, you would've asked.

30:45.302 --> 30:49.136
<i>The reason I hired you, Crews, is 'cause
I knew you could get the job done.</i>

30:49.222 --> 30:51.463
<i>But if you can't handle
Red, you tell me now.</i>

30:52.184 --> 30:54.175
<i>I want those
guns tonight!</i>

30:54.269 --> 30:56.226
<i>Now, you just go back and get
in that truck and do the job</i>

30:56.313 --> 30:58.554
I'm paying you to do, because I
don't think your parole officer

30:58.648 --> 31:01.060
is gonna be nearly as
understanding as I am.

31:01.151 --> 31:02.767
Do you understand
what I'm sayin', Jack?

31:02.861 --> 31:04.522
<i>I'll do what I have to.</i>

31:06.656 --> 31:08.146
(SIGHS)
(PHONE BEEPS)

31:11.995 --> 31:13.702
This guy's
gonna be trouble.

31:15.165 --> 31:16.246
All right, Tiny.

31:16.333 --> 31:18.415
They hit us once,

31:18.502 --> 31:20.288
they might try it again.

31:21.004 --> 31:24.292
You know, I was thinkin',
we could switch to I-85.

31:24.549 --> 31:26.836
There's a turnoff
about 20 miles up.

31:27.511 --> 31:30.629
That way, if Red comes back, we
won't be where he thinks we'll be.

31:32.307 --> 31:34.048
Sonny, you ride with me.

31:34.351 --> 31:35.807
Let's do it.

31:37.604 --> 31:41.063
Crews? Wait a minute!
You think I was in on this?

31:41.691 --> 31:43.056
Crossed my mind. Yeah.

31:43.151 --> 31:44.482
I wasn't. I swear.

31:44.569 --> 31:47.152
Red never tells me anything.
You can ask anybody.

31:47.906 --> 31:49.647
Earl, you got that right.

31:49.741 --> 31:52.199
Hey, man, they were
shootin' at me too!

31:53.370 --> 31:55.862
You ever thought about bein'
a professional singer?

31:56.915 --> 31:58.121
Don't.

31:59.292 --> 32:00.908
Did I miss something?

32:01.336 --> 32:02.701
Get in the car, Wes.

32:05.757 --> 32:06.872
Tried to sing you songs?

32:06.967 --> 32:08.457
Ugh...

32:08.552 --> 32:11.044
Well, no wonder you want
the pleasure of my company.

32:17.519 --> 32:19.476
(ENGINE REVS)

32:23.692 --> 32:25.399
(TIRES SCREECHING)

32:27.904 --> 32:29.486
FORD: Okay, they're
on the move again.

32:29.573 --> 32:31.814
First sign of trouble,
I'm bringing them in.

32:33.243 --> 32:36.406
There's over $3 million in
automatic weapons on that truck.

32:36.496 --> 32:37.611
I know that.

32:37.706 --> 32:40.789
Then you know the array of tragedy
those guns are going to inflict

32:40.876 --> 32:42.037
when they hit
the streets of Jersey?

32:42.127 --> 32:44.243
I want the man who
puts them on the streets.

32:44.337 --> 32:46.999
We don't take him out, he'll have
$3 million in automatic weapons

32:47.090 --> 32:49.752
comin' up from Georgia
this time next week.

32:49.885 --> 32:53.970
I mean, that might keep you in a
job, but it's not the solution.

32:54.055 --> 32:57.173
Guy driving is Jack Philip Crews.
Did two years in Bayside.

32:57.267 --> 33:00.259
Thatsoundshke just the kind of man you
want hauling a load of artillery.

33:00.353 --> 33:02.344
No priors. He was
released three weeks ago,

33:02.439 --> 33:03.600
early parole
for good behavior.

33:03.940 --> 33:04.896
Looks like
he's just the driver.

33:04.983 --> 33:06.690
What'd he do his time for?

33:06.776 --> 33:08.107
Vehicular manslaughter.

33:08.278 --> 33:09.518
Thank you.

33:12.699 --> 33:14.360
(RINGING)

33:16.661 --> 33:18.243
Crews residence.
CREWS: Hey, <i>little</i> one.

33:18.330 --> 33:20.071
<i>Dam
So, how was school?</i>

33:20.165 --> 33:24.124
Great. We had a half a day. Are you still
gonna help me with my free throws tonight?

33:24.211 --> 33:27.044
Well, I, uh...
I can't tonight, honey.

33:27.130 --> 33:29.667
If I wanna buy you those
high-tops, I gotta work late.

33:29.758 --> 33:31.840
But no way
I'm missing your game.

33:31.927 --> 33:33.884
<i>So, can I speak to your mom?</i>

33:33.970 --> 33:35.301
Yeah.

33:35.972 --> 33:37.337
Mom.

33:37.432 --> 33:39.014
Tracy, go get your
homework started, okay?

33:39.100 --> 33:40.386
Okay-

33:41.478 --> 33:43.560
Jack? Where are you?

33:44.147 --> 33:45.854
<i>North</i> Carolina.

33:45.941 --> 33:48.649
<i>Look, I know you didn't
want me to do this but,</i>

33:49.319 --> 33:51.686
Melanie, I can't
letuslosethathouse.

33:52.822 --> 33:56.190
<i>I think we both know this is
about more than the house, Jack.</i>

33:56.785 --> 33:58.526
It's about you.

33:59.538 --> 34:03.907
(SIGHS) Well, I'll be home <i>as</i>
soon <i>as</i> I can. I love you.

34:06.211 --> 34:07.542
Be careful.

34:11.341 --> 34:13.047
(PHONE BEEPS)

34:15.428 --> 34:16.839
(BEEPS)

34:38.994 --> 34:40.405
How long you been
drivin' trucks?

34:40.911 --> 34:42.949
Since I was 18.

34:43.039 --> 34:44.871
Not much for school, huh?

34:44.958 --> 34:46.197
Had to make a living.

34:48.168 --> 34:50.581
I was gonna be a football player
before I screwed up my knee.

34:51.214 --> 34:53.420
So, now you run guns
instead of footballs.

34:55.510 --> 34:57.877
I'm gonna make me
some serious money.

34:57.971 --> 34:59.882
Buy a house on the lake.

34:59.973 --> 35:01.384
Hell, I might
even buy me a lake.

35:03.935 --> 35:06.848
Find a nice little honey,
settle down.

35:06.938 --> 35:08.178
How about you?
You got big dreams?

35:09.316 --> 35:11.307
I'm workin' on it.

35:12.569 --> 35:13.775
CREWSI Oh, shi...

35:14.571 --> 35:15.936
What's wrong?

35:16.740 --> 35:19.198
There's a weigh station
on both of these roads.

35:19.576 --> 35:21.487
One of 'em
is bound to be open.

35:21.578 --> 35:23.364
So, we got a 50-50 chance.

35:23.496 --> 35:24.736
That's right.

35:25.957 --> 35:27.539
Earl said take 85.

35:38.094 --> 35:41.678
Where the hell is he goin'?
I told him not to take 26.

35:49.522 --> 35:50.762
(SIGHS)

36:00.325 --> 36:03.317
MAN: Okay, let's see
your next set of axles.

36:04.287 --> 36:06.073
Hold it there.

36:09.626 --> 36:10.661
Pull forward, driver.

36:10.960 --> 36:12.450
<i>(ON PA) Next two.</i>

36:18.635 --> 36:20.546
(ENGINE IDLING)
Gonna go grab a smoke.

36:33.024 --> 36:34.480
<i>Pull forward, driver.</i>

36:49.374 --> 36:51.160
How are you, sir?
All right. How are you?

36:51.376 --> 36:52.491
Okay-

36:53.211 --> 36:55.418
You know you got
a headlight out up there?

36:55.505 --> 36:56.870
What'd ya do to
your front end?

36:56.965 --> 36:58.547
She was that way
when I picked her up.

36:58.633 --> 36:59.873
It's not my usual rig.

37:01.010 --> 37:02.842
<i>Pull up, driver.
Next two.</i>

37:08.852 --> 37:10.217
Hold it there.

37:12.105 --> 37:14.142
(AIR BRAKES HISSING)

37:18.236 --> 37:21.194
Hey, uh... Bobby Lewis
still work here?

37:21.281 --> 37:22.442
Big guy. Wrestler.

37:22.574 --> 37:23.814
You talkin' about Pooh Bear.

37:23.908 --> 37:25.444
Pooh Bear... Yeah.

37:25.535 --> 37:27.742
No. He took a private job

37:27.829 --> 37:30.537
down in Orlando
about a year ago now.

37:31.249 --> 37:33.286
So, you haven't made this
run in a while, have you?

37:33.376 --> 37:35.037
No, sir, not in
a couple of years.

37:36.880 --> 37:38.211
Pull forward, driver.

37:40.175 --> 37:43.088
(ENGINE REVS)

37:44.846 --> 37:47.053
(AIR BRAKES HISS)

37:52.187 --> 37:53.552
You're right at the limit.

37:54.105 --> 37:55.470
Aw, you know these guys.

37:55.565 --> 37:57.556
They try to wring
every dollar from a load.

37:58.651 --> 38:00.392
You pull for
this outfit often?

38:00.487 --> 38:01.818
Not when I can help it.

38:02.739 --> 38:04.980
Got a load of bathroom
fixtures, huh?

38:05.074 --> 38:06.610
Yeah. Toilets.
(CHUCKLES)

38:10.914 --> 38:12.825
I tell you what. Why don't
you pull up right over there,

38:12.916 --> 38:14.577
and I'm just gonna take
a quick look in the back.

38:15.502 --> 38:16.708
All right. Will do.

38:35.188 --> 38:36.553
Yeah. Yeah.

38:36.648 --> 38:38.264
Hlgetback
with you later.

38:39.442 --> 38:40.978
Who you talkin' to?

38:42.821 --> 38:44.277
My mother.

38:45.073 --> 38:46.939
Your mother, my ass.

38:47.617 --> 38:50.575
She's in a cancer ward
at Good Samaritan in Philly.

38:50.662 --> 38:53.745
You wanna give 'em a call?
Ask for Nadine Boxer.

38:55.375 --> 38:56.911
Don't keep her
on the phone too long.

38:57.001 --> 38:58.787
She doesn't have
a lot of strength left.

39:01.172 --> 39:03.459
Here.
Good Samaritan.

39:21.818 --> 39:23.183
SONNY: What's goin' on?

39:24.362 --> 39:26.319
They wanted to take a look.

39:33.663 --> 39:37.281
I've hauled a lot of things, but this
is a first for a truckload of shitters.

39:37.375 --> 39:40.834
Yeah, it smells like somebody's
already been usin' some of 'em.

39:46.467 --> 39:48.674
(RINGING)
Highway Patrol.

40:06.321 --> 40:09.859
(TINY BARKS)

40:10.533 --> 40:11.944
Does that dog belong to you?

40:12.035 --> 40:13.366
No. He came with the load.

40:14.537 --> 40:15.618
(SNARLS)
OFFICER: Jim!

40:16.205 --> 40:18.037
Hey, Jim!
Yeah!

40:18.124 --> 40:19.956
I need to talk to you
for a minute.

40:20.043 --> 40:21.374
(TINY GROWLS)

40:24.547 --> 40:26.584
You put a leash
on that dog.

40:27.008 --> 40:28.624
(GROWLING)

40:34.599 --> 40:36.385
(SNARLING)

40:39.896 --> 40:40.977
Something is...

40:41.481 --> 40:42.812
What?

40:42.899 --> 40:45.766
I get the feeling somebody
wanted us to get through here.

40:49.781 --> 40:53.319
That was too close. You played this
thing with no margin for error.

40:53.952 --> 40:57.070
You should always leave a margin.
You've got to have margins.

40:57.163 --> 40:58.995
Do me a favor,
huh, therapy boy?

40:59.082 --> 41:01.824
Work your unresolved stress
out later in group.

41:02.085 --> 41:04.167
This is a control issue
for you, isn't it, Allen?

41:04.253 --> 41:06.711
This is a surveillance
operation, McClaren.

41:06.798 --> 41:07.833
There are layers.

41:07.924 --> 41:09.710
Oh... Layers.

41:10.802 --> 41:12.588
What else do we know
about the driver?

41:12.679 --> 41:14.010
He works the Jersey docks.

41:14.097 --> 41:15.758
He's got a wife
and kid in Millburn.

41:29.946 --> 41:32.608
That phone call you made
before, that was your wife?

41:36.202 --> 41:37.863
Didn't tell her you
was comin', did you?

41:38.413 --> 41:40.120
Let's just say, uh,

41:40.206 --> 41:42.243
she doesn't like it
when I drive.

41:44.794 --> 41:47.377
Yeah, well, it must
be nice to be missed.

41:48.297 --> 41:49.458
You got any pictures?

41:51.300 --> 41:52.711
Yeah, I know
you got some pictures.

41:52.802 --> 41:54.918
Come on.
Come with the pictures.

42:02.603 --> 42:03.934
Ah!

42:04.022 --> 42:05.558
Little girl too.

42:06.607 --> 42:08.097
Nice-looking family.

42:08.776 --> 42:10.687
Can't be mad
at you for that.

42:14.073 --> 42:15.689
(CHUCKLES)

42:16.117 --> 42:18.154
So, let me ask you
a question, man.

42:19.162 --> 42:22.951
How come you doin' this? I mean,
you know, you got a nice family.

42:23.374 --> 42:24.864
Must make
good money drivin'.

42:27.170 --> 42:29.207
Know that dream
you were talkin' about?

42:32.216 --> 42:34.002
I'm about
to lose mine.

42:38.014 --> 42:40.381
Tracy, you ready
to go to the store?

42:40.767 --> 42:42.098
(KNOCKING)

42:42.685 --> 42:44.471
(SIGHS) Who is it?

42:44.562 --> 42:46.303
Department of Corrections.

42:47.190 --> 42:48.680
(SIGHS)

42:50.902 --> 42:51.937
Hi.
Hi.

42:52.028 --> 42:54.395
I'm Grady Cooper, your
husband's parole officer.

42:58.367 --> 43:00.074
Could I see
some l.D., please?

43:00.703 --> 43:02.614
(CHUCKLES)
(GASPS) on!

43:02.872 --> 43:03.862
(SCREAMS)

43:03.956 --> 43:05.037
(GRUNTING)

43:06.125 --> 43:07.206
Tracy!

43:09.128 --> 43:10.163
Tracy!

43:11.172 --> 43:12.162
Where are you?

43:13.341 --> 43:14.297
Tracy!

43:14.383 --> 43:15.373
(POUNDING)

